In 2018, Rhythm Unplugged was started by Flytime Music as a multi-day indoor concert to allow people to come together with one thing in mind: Music This year marks the 7th year of this concert. Eko Convention Centre in Lagos, Nigeria will be the venue for the event, and it will be 5 days long; starting from the 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd and 25th December 2019. On 20th December 2019, American rapper and songwriter; Mase and Jamaican Reggae singer, songwriter, rapper; Koffee and several other acts will grace the stage to wow over 5,000 attendees. The popular Boyz II Men who are known for their American R&B will be present on 21st December 2019 to take the audience down memory lane as they perform ‘End of the Road’, ‘I’ll Make Love to You’ and many more. The glamour continues on 22nd December 2019 where Nigeria’s new unique sound with artists that are showcasing their musical freedom will be on stage. The newest franchise to the Flytime Festival lineup with also star the hottest girl of the summer, American rapper, singer and songwriter; Megan Thee Stallion. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1048230 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-597x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1283" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-597x598.jpg 597w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-487x488.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-239x240.jpg 239w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-479x480.jpg 479w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1-600x600.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/MEGAN-THEE-STALLION-1.jpg 858w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />  Tiwa Savage will also be present as she headlines DAY 4, 23rd December 2019. The theme for the day will be “Everything Savage.” She will take the crowd through her musical journey with songs like ‘Love Me’, ‘Kele Kele Love’ to the recent chart-topper; ‘49-99’. The festival’s last day which is 25th December will be shut down as the evening holds one of the biggest headlining concerts Lagos has ever seen by a captivating show by a yet-to-be-disclosed, world-renowned, A-list Nigerian Artist. Flytime Promotions treats guests to the biggest Christmas concert ever.